=== Etymology ===
from Greek meaning "witness".

== [[noun]] ==
#Someone who suffers or is killed due to his or her beliefs.
#:''Stephen died as a martyr for supporting the belief in Jesus Christ''.
#(Martyr to) one who suffers greatly
#:''Stephen was a martyr to arthritis.

== [[verb]] ==
to martyr

#Put to death as a martyr.

